Colombia Would Consider Foreign Borrowing Controls, Cano Says

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-04-06T17:32:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/colombia-would-consider-foreign-borrowing-controls-cano-says.html
Colombia  would consider imposing
capital controls should the central bank see “excessive”
short-term borrowing from abroad, bank director Carlos Gustavo Cano said.  That isn’t currently the case, Cano told reporters in
Bogota.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
